The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Have a good chance in World Cup, says Murali
                                                                                                                       7                                      Have a good chance in World Cup, says Murali
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Spin wizard Muttiah Muralidharan feels that Sri Lanka have a good chance of winning the World Cup as it will be held in the sub-continent this time.         
	Im excited about this years ICC Cricket World Cup which being held in the sub-continent. Last time it was played in the sub-continent, we won the trophy. We have a good side and hopefully we will have a good chance this time too, Muralidharan said in this weeks ICC Cricket World audio show.         
	He further added: Its a big event and people are excited about hosting part of the tournament in Sri Lanka. We are thrilled as Sri Lanka will be hosting a semi-final.         
	In the same ICC show, former England medium pacer Angus Fraser, said: It was an honour to be contacted by the ICC to help judge who should be part of the long lists for the ICC Awards.         
	He also said: It was an extremely difficult task with some outstanding performances deserving to be on the lists. I was particularly pleased to be able to nominate someone like South Africas Hashim Amla, who has done particularly well in Test cricket this year but has also shone in the one-day format of the game.                                                                                                                     
